[SN]TITLE[SN]
David Raya: Blackburn Rovers goalkeeper extends contract

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Blackburn Rovers goalkeeper David Raya has signed a new one-year contract extension to keep him at the Championship club until 2019.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The Spaniard, 21, joined Rovers in 2012 from Cornella and has made 12 appearances for the Lancashire side.
He spent time on loan at National League side Southport in 2014.
"I'm obviously very happy here. I've been here since I was 16 and it feels like home," he told Blackburn's club website.
